SIMPLE: roussette
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roussette
<hw>Rous*sette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; -- so called
in allusion to the color. See <er>Russet</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fruit bat, especially the large species
(<spn>Pieropus vulgaris</spn>) inhabiting the islands of the Indian
ocean. It measures about a yard across the expanded wings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any small shark of the genus
<gen>Scyllium</gen>; -- called also <altname>dogfish</altname>. See
<er>Dogfish</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roust</ent>⟦br⟧
